node.text:
You become what you constantly feed your mind with.

If you constantly feed your mind with, “I can’t afford that, I can’t be rich, I can’t do that...”

Well guess what, you’re right.

Instead of telling yourself statements, which only closes the mind.

Change it to: “HOW can I afford that?”, “How can I be rich?”, “How can I do that?”. 

This will broaden your mind and you will start to think of solutions to your problem rather than excuses.

Did you find this helpful? Follow @savetoinvest for more!

#robertkiyosaki #moneymindset #richmindset #richmind #mindsetshift #changeyourmindset #savetoinvest

node.text:
It's not an easy task, but the strategy is simple.⁠
⁠
If you consistently invest $10,000/year into an ETF that mirrors the S&P 500 which has averaged an annual return of 10% since 1962, you'll be worth over $4,4M in 40 years.⁠
⁠
And as the world is getting wealthier and more people are investing, I believe this number will be even higher in the future.⁠
⁠
What are your thoughts on this?⁠
Comment below! 💭⁠
⁠
Note: This post is NOT factoring in the average inflation rate of 2.5%. With that in mind, $4,4M is not going to be as valuable as it is today.
⁠
Follow 👉 @savetoinvest for more!⁠
⁠

node.text:
People often ask, "what type of assets can I invest in?"

There are many types of assets out there, some with high risk & high returns like cryptos, NFTs, and individual stocks.

And some which are considered more steady and safe, like gold, bonds & real estate.

You'd want to stay diversified across multiple assets. And as you go, you invest more in those performing well and let the nonperformers go.
